**Managing Game Modes**

I'm now implementing the mode selection logic, including stopping the sync poll on mode changes. I'm focusing on ensuring seamless transitions between game modes, specifically stopping the sync polling when switching out of online multiplayer. I'm prioritizing data integrity and efficient resource management.

```javascript
document.querySelectorAll('.mode-tab').forEach(tab => {
  tab.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
    document.querySelectorAll('.mode-tab').forEach(t => t.classList.remove('active'));
    tab.classList.add('active');

    // Stop sync poll if running
    if (syncInterval) {
      clearInterval(syncInterval);
      syncInterval = null;
    }

    gameMode = tab.dataset.mode;

    // Additional logic needed here to handle mode-specific functionality

  });
});
